{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelProtocol"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"buffered"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","title":"set(buffered:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:4GLib17IOChannelProtocolPAAE3set8bufferedySb_tF"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The buffering state can only be set if the channel’s encoding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":". For any other encoding, the channel must be buffered."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelprotocol\/set(buffered:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelProtocol\/set(buffered:)"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"buffered","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A buffered channel can only be set unbuffered if the channel’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"internal buffers have been flushed. Newly created channels or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"channels which have returned "},{"code":"eof","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not require such a flush. For write-only channels, a call to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"g_io_channel_flush () is sufficient. For all other channels,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the buffers may be flushed by a call to g_io_channel_seek_position ()."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This includes the possibility of seeking with seek type "},{"code":"cur","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and an offset of zero. Note that this means that socket-based","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"channels cannot be set unbuffered once they have had data","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"read from them."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On unbuffered channels, it is safe to mix read and write","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calls from the new and old APIs, if this is necessary for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"maintaining old code."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default state of the channel is buffered."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","title":"MainContext","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannelProtocol/set(buffered:)":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"buffered"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"title":"set(buffered:)","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelprotocol\/set(buffered:)","abstract":[{"text":"The buffering state can only be set if the channel’s encoding","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For any other encoding, the channel must be buffered.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelProtocol\/set(buffered:)","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannelProtocol":{"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"IOChannelProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelprotocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"IOChannelProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"IOChannelProtocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelProtocol","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOChannel"},{"type":"text","text":" data type aims to provide a portable method for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using file descriptors, pipes, and sockets, and integrating them"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"into the main event loop (see [struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"]). Currently,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"full support is available on UNIX platforms; support for Windows"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is only partially complete."}]}}}